column1: # Name: Share of labour force with secondary education, Male

# Definition: Share of males in the labour force age 15+ in upper secondary and post-secondary non-tertiary education programmes that are usually restricted to students who have completed the 8-9 years of basic education or that straddle the boundary between upper-secondary and post-secondary education.
# Source: International Labour Organization (ILO) Key Indicators of the Labour Market (KILM)
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
